---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../data/siteConfig';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Digital Infrastructure Specialist">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    
    {/* Hero Section */}
    <Hero 
      title="Who I Am. What I Do. Why It Exists."
      subtitle="This business is built on one belief — that a small business in Kerala deserves the same technical foundation that large brands take for granted."
      showCTA={false}
    />

    {/* Philosophy Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">The Philosophy</h2>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Most people who build websites are in the business of making things look good. That is not this business.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            This business is built on one belief — that a small business in Kerala deserves the same technical foundation that large brands take for granted. The ability to be found. The ability to be trusted. The ability to exist in the places where their customers are looking, whether that is Google Search, Google Maps, or an AI that someone asked for a recommendation.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            A website is not a product. It is infrastructure. And infrastructure either works correctly or it fails quietly. Most Kerala small business sites are failing quietly right now and nobody is telling them.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            This business tells them. Then fixes it. Then makes sure it stays fixed.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-xl p-8 my-8">
            <p class="text-xl font-medium mb-4">The work is not about:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300">
              <li>• Design trends or clever copy</li>
              <li>• Social media presence</li>
              <li>• Marketing campaigns</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-4">The work is about:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-300">
              <li>• Building the technical foundation</li>
              <li>• Making businesses permanently discoverable</li>
              <li>• Making businesses permanently credible</li>
              <li>• Giving businesses control of their digital presence</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-lg mt-6 text-slate-400 italic">
              "That restraint is intentional. Doing one thing with complete integrity is worth more than doing five things averagely."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Vision Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">The Vision</h2>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            To become the most trusted name for digital presence infrastructure among small businesses in Kerala. Not the biggest. Not the loudest. The most trusted.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            A business that any Kerala homestay owner, clinic, or local service provider can approach and know with certainty that what gets built for them will be technically correct, honestly priced, and built to last without dependency or ongoing fees they did not agree to.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            A solo operation that proves you do not need a team, a big office, or a loud brand to deliver results that matter. That one person with the right knowledge, the right tools, and the right values can build something quietly essential in a specific community.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-6 rounded-r-lg my-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-900 mb-4">In Five Years</h3>
            <p class="text-green-800">
              The vision is not scale. It is depth. Deeper knowledge of one or two verticals. Stronger relationships in a specific geography. A reputation that travels entirely by word of mouth because the work speaks clearly enough that no advertising is needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* What The Work Is Not Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">What The Work Is Not</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-red-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-red-900 mb-4">We Don't Do:</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
              <li>• Off-page SEO (backlinks, outreach)</li>
              <li>• Paid advertising (Meta, Google ads)</li>
              <li>• Social media management</li>
              <li>• WordPress development</li>
              <li>• Complex web applications</li>
              <li>• Maintenance retainers with locked contracts</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-green-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900 mb-4">Why These Boundaries Exist:</h3>
            <p class="text-green-800 leading-relaxed">
              Every boundary exists for the same reason. Doing fewer things with complete integrity produces better results and a more sustainable business than doing everything averagely.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Protection Strategy Section */}
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">The Protection Strategy</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Vertical Depth Over Breadth</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Spending concentrated time in one or two business categories until the domain knowledge is deep enough that no generalist competitor can match it.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Community Presence Over Marketing</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Being genuinely known and trusted in a specific Kerala geography through relationships, referrals, and consistent results. This is slow to build and nearly impossible to replicate.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">The Advisory Position Over Time</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Moving from the person who builds sites to the person clients call before they make any digital decision. That relationship is earned through trust over multiple engagements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">The Human Layer That AI Cannot Replace</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-700">
              Judgment, interpretation, presence, accountability, and trust in a relationship-driven market. These compound over time. They do not depreciate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


  </main>
</Layout>
